commit.message:
cmd: Update carapace code

The carapace library has add FilterParts() to replace
Filter(c.Parts).ToA().

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/mr_discussion.go: Switch from NotePosition to PositionOptions

The new gitlab library version uses PositionOptions and replaces
NotePosition.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd: Replace Labels with LabelOptions

The gitlab library is now using LabelOptions instead of Labels.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

internal/gitlab/gitlab.go: Update for new version of gitlab library

Fix some compilation issues introduced by the new gitlab library version.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

lab: Update additional packages and vendor file

ie) go get -u ./...; go mod vendor; git commit

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

build(deps): bump golang.org/x/crypto from 0.9.0 to 0.17.0

Bumps [golang.org/x/crypto](https://github.com/golang/crypto) from 0.9.0 to 0.17.0.
- [Commits](https://github.com/golang/crypto/compare/v0.9.0...v0.17.0)

---
updated-dependencies:
- dependency-name: golang.org/x/crypto
  dependency-type: direct:production
...

Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

gitlab: Fix other limits issues

As explained in the previous commit, there are instances in which
the incorrect number of items were returned.  Fix up two other instances
of the same issue in the Project snippet and Issue list code.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

gitlab: Fix 'mr list' limits

The command 'lab mr list --author $author_name --state merged' was
returning a list of 100 for each engineer on a project.  Evidence in the
git tree showed that this was not the case (most had more than 100).

This was due to a calcluational error in the MRList() code.  Implement a
new algorithm that correctly returns all MRs instead of the last 100.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
feat(milestone): Add `milestone browse` subcommand
feat(miletone create): Add --start and --due flags

docs: update scoop installation note

Since available in scoop/main bucket.
ensure gitlab API requests are canceled if user hits control-c

cmd/mr_list_test.go: Update latestCreatedTestMR

Update the value of latestCreatedTestMR.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/mr_note_test.go: Fix mrCommentSlashDiscussionDumpsterID

The existing mrCommentSlashDiscussionDumpsterID MR, 3953, is now reporting
errors

mr_discussion.go:174: POST https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/lab-testing/test/merge_requests/3953/discussions: 400 {message: 400 Bad request - Note {:base=>["Maximum number of comments exceeded"]}

Create a new MR for testing notes and discussions.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
remove --branch on project browse command

cmd/mr_create.go: Fix -f option

The -f option was reported to be broken.  This occurred due to a coding
error and this simple change will fix it.

Fix the -f option (-F and no options have also been verified to work).

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/project_browse.go: Add --file and --branch options

@sding3 has requested the ability to browse to a specific file using a
--file argument.  In addition to this I think it is a good idea to also
add a --branch argument so users can browse a file on a specific branch.

Add --file and --branch options.

Close #866

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/token_test.go: Remove test code

GitLab only allows administrators to create tokens via the API.  This is
strange given that users can create tokens in the WebUI without any
issues.

Remove some of the test code.  Hopefully one day this commit can be
reverted and the test code can be executed.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/token_test.go: Add testing

Add token command testing for create, list, and revoke.  This is best done
in a single test where a token is created, listed, and then revoked.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

cmd/mr_show.go: Provide a better error value for 'MR not found'

@sding3 points out a valid case for a unique error return in #847.

Provide a better error value when a branch doesn't have an associated MR.

Close #847

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
fix(token): Show help when no subcommand given

lab: Add token support

Add support for showing the current token, listing all of a user's tokens,
revoking tokens, and creating tokens (creating tokens is limited by the
GitLab API to Administrator level only).

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
test: Update tests for changes to fixture project
feat(mr list): Support `--reviewer=any/none

refactor(mr list): Rename variable

This is more consitent with the other `*ID` vars.
feat(mr list): Add `--approver` option
feat(issue/mr list): Support `--assignee=any/none`
feat(issue/mr list): Support `--milestone=any/none`

internal/config/config.go: Warn on expiring tokens

82444bfa9c07 ("config: Add config verification") added some simple
checking to see if a user's token was valid.  After the recent go module
updates we can now use the PersonalAccessToken service from go-gitlab to
warn a user that their token is about to expire.  This warning should
happen once a day when the config is verified.

Warn a user when their token is going to expire within two weeks.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>

Makefile: Update internal-test

After the modules update, the internal-test target no longer worked
properly and returned a

gocovmerge coverage-*.out > coverage.txt && rm coverage-*.out
/bin/sh: 1: gocovmerge: not found

error when running travisCI.  This is because the full path to the
gocovmerge executable has to specified.

Fix the installation and execution of gocovmerge.

Signed-off-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
